reviews.review_text:
Scarlet>Fire oh so good Yes, I was at these shows. This was the real deal for 91'.  Pine Knob was really a great place to see a show. On this night, everything was in sync.  The red/blue lightning paper added to the scheme of things, as well as all things Summer Tour. Spent the first set half way between the seats and the lawn.  The sound was GREAT and everyone was off to a good start.  
The Stranger opener, while not the longest version, sure pack a punch and put everyone in a grooving mood.  
The meat and potatoes of this fine show is the Scarlet>Fire! No doubt, this was a very special version.  The sound bouncing off the coned roof of the Reserved section and swirling up and over the lawn section was magical.  So the journey began.  The Other One rocked, Stella Blue finding it's way out of space just added to the unique feeling of that night.

Summer 91 Rocked Download this and zero in on the They Love Eachother.  Great version for that era.  Crank at high volumes to enjoy the interplay between Jerry and Bruce and Vince.  The crowd reactions are classic during Jerry's first few verses of the chorus and continue to react throughout the song.  STRONG WINNING!  It's as good four strong bloody mary's before 2pm.  Great sound quality. The band is ON.
